5|$|Principal {{photography}} for Charlie and the <b>Chocolate</b> Factory {{started on}} June 21, 2004 at Pinewood Studios in England. Director Tim Burton and composer Danny Elfman found filming somewhat difficult {{because they were}} simultaneously working on Corpse Bride. The Wonka Factory exterior was coincidentally constructed on the same backlot Burton had used for Gotham City in Batman (1989). The ceremonial scene required 500 local extras. The <b>Chocolate</b> Room/River setpiece filled Pinewood's 007 Stage. As a consequence of British Equity rules, which state that children can only work {{four and a half}} hours a day, filming for Charlie and the <b>Chocolate</b> Factory took six months, ending in December 2004.|$|E
